# Adapters: Conceptual Naming

Name adapter files by **concept/role**, not by the underlying technology.

## Do

- **database.adapter.ts** — persistence/ORM (even if implemented with Drizzle)
- **cache.adapter.ts** — caching (even if implemented with Redis)
- **queue.adapter.ts** — job queues (even if implemented with Redis/BullMQ)
- **embedder.adapter.ts** — embeddings
- **storage.adapter.ts** — blob/file storage
- **scraper.adapter.ts** — scraping/crawling
- **messaging.adapter.ts** — messaging/notifications

## Don’t

- **drizzle.adapter.ts** → use `database.adapter.ts`
- **redis.adapter.ts** → use `cache.adapter.ts` and/or `queue.adapter.ts` (separate concepts)
- **bullmq.adapter.ts** → use `queue.adapter.ts`
- **s3.adapter.ts** → use `storage.adapter.ts`

## Pattern

`{concept}.adapter.ts` where **concept** is the protocol role (database, cache, queue, etc.), not the library or service name. Tests: `{concept}.adapter.spec.ts`.
